			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">All Bards are not created equal, a Bards take on creation.<a name="40064"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 15 04 4:05 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>So, young one, You wish to join the ranks of the bard? Well you have chosen one of the hardest lives on Norrath. You must know more of the lands of Norrath, the Moon Luclin and the outer planes than any other. You are forever traveling, singing for your meals and ale, and most likely your place of sleep. Saddly, even with all the skills and songs we can do, many of us still have trouble getting in or even keeping with a good group ( not for lack of tring ) so we must also learn the art of soloing. Now I know many of my brothers and sisters will say that as a bard you can not solo past, say 35ish. Well this is wrong. A Good bard with the proper stats can solo at all tiers ( levels ) . Now, should I run out of room on this post I shall pick up on the next, and so on. Best of luck to you, my young friend, and May ALL the gods of Norrath and beyond watch over you. 
<br />

<br />
Starting Stats Point Spread : 
<br />
Grouping Bard ONLY:
<br />

<br />
Wood Elf : 10 Chr, 10 Dex, 5 Str
<br />
Half Elf : 10 Chr, 10 Str , 5 Dex
<br />
Human : 10 Chr, 10 Dex, 5 Str
<br />
Vah Shir : 15 Dex , 10 Chr
<br />

<br />
Solo Bards ONLY: 
<br />
Wood Elf : 25 Sta ( Str and Dex items are easy to get )
<br />
Half Elf : 20 Sta , 5 Str ( or Int if you want to learn things abit faster )
<br />
Human : 15 Sta , 5 Agi , 5 Dex
<br />
Vah Shir : 15 Sta, 5 Dex , 5 Wis ( or you can do the full 10 Dex )
<br />
Notice that for a solo bard the STA stat plays a larger role than with a grouping bard. The reason for this is that you , as a soloer, will have to fight longer and harder than your grouping counterpart so a marked differance needs be made. You can make up your short commings with gear later so dont worry.
<br />

<br />
Skills: 
<br />
Weapons skills all seem to have maxed out at skill 200 for now. But at 50th and above they will go up again 25 points more. Hand to Hand, on the other hand * grin* , seems to stay at 100 skill points forever. and Throwing at 113
<br />
Insterment Skills will all forever max at 235 ( this happens at level 46 for those of you that will work to keep them up ). Note : DO NOT train in Brass until your 18th tier for that is when you get your first Brass song. Its a differance of 7 training points, but you'll see when ( and if ) you follow this advice.
<br />
Other Skills: 
<br />
10 Dodge : 125 / 155
<br />
10 Meditate : 1 / 1
<br />
10 Pick Lock : 125 / 125
<br />
12 Forage : 55 / 55
<br />
15 Sense Traps : 120 / 120
<br />
17 Dual Wield : 210 / 210
<br />
17 Sneak : 75 / 75
<br />
24 Safe Fall : 40 / 40
<br />
25 Hide : 40 / 40 
<br />
26 Instill Doubt : 100 / 100 ( you can only get this skill in FP ) 
<br />
30 Disarm Traps : 120 / 120
<br />
35 Track : 100 / 100 ( send in feedback, we need this skill updated ) 
<br />
53 Parry : 75 / 75
<br />
58 Riposte : 70 / 70
<br />
Language Skills : There are 25 Languages out there, all max at 100 skill points.
<br />
Insterment skills:
<br />
1 Singing : 235
<br />
5 Percussion : 235
<br />
8 String : 235
<br />
11 Brass : 235 ( but save until 18th to get the extra points ) 
<br />
14 Wind : 235
<br />
Trade Skills:
<br />
Blacksmithing : 200
<br />
Brewing : 200
<br />
Cooking : 200
<br />
Fletching : 200
<br />
Jewellery : 200
<br />
Pottery : 200
<br />
Tailoring : 200
<br />
(Note: only ONE skill can exceed 200 unless you spend the AA points to change that ) 
<br />
Also note that some of these skill points may differ due to your race. Just keep that in mind.
<br />
1 Alcohol Tolerance : 200/ 200
<br />
1 Beg : 200 / 200 ( but why would any bard want to? ) 
<br />
1 Fishing : 200 / 200 ( dont spill your beer ) 
<br />
1 Sense Heading : 200 / 200 ( LEARN THIS! ) 
<br />
1 Swimming : 200 / 200
<br />
1 Bind Wound : 150 / 200 ( good skill to have ) 
<br />
Any and All songs are listed on EQ-Castersrealm.com and should be printed out. Any further questions please contact me in game. But the last piece of advice I can give any of you, my younger brothers and sisters, is to get up and keep up your defense skill ( level max is 5 times level ) . Best of luck to you one and all * bow* and may you never miss a note.
<br />
P.S. 
<br />
Many songs you can just sing even is an insterment skill is listed. but keep this in mind, if you dont practice that insterment you can not ever sing that song. You'll not know the notes unless you do. So keep up on them.
<br />
Hello again my brothers and sisters * bow * 
<br />
Well this time I thought I might give alittle more advice for those of you that have the resourses to gain weapons and armor at such a young and tender tier.
<br />
Weapons:
<br />
Weapons should not go up past a DMG of 7 or 8 as the mobs you fight at lower levels will die FAR to fast to get your weapon skill up. So keep this in mind, also this does not mean that if you see a great deal on an uber weapon not to get it just put it away till you get your skill up to use it.
<br />
Armor:
<br />
Many have asked me what makes the best starting armor for a young bard. Well Lambiant is outstanding but getting harder for find right off the bat. The armor I would choose to fit the bill is head to toe RyGorr ( once you wash the orc smell out ) it makes GREAT starting armor and ups your stats in a nice way. Its is one of the most sold armor types in the bazaar and the cost of it seems to be coming down. So Keep this in mind. If you want armor that seems to be good up to about 50 and you wish to get it not and not have to bother with it for along time check out the Gothic Plate Armor. The stats on it are not TOO bad and the price is not out of most ball parks. Meaning you can pick most of this up for 500p or less per piece.
<br />
Well now, Here I am yet again. I seem to have more and more young bardlings coming to me and asking where are the best places to hunt solo and at what tiers. Well in this post tis my hope to answer this question as best I can, so read on and learn well. ( and best of luck to you all as well ) 
<br />
1-5 newbie zone ( either Qeynos or Freeport seem the easy way as higher ups seem to be about in times of need ) 
<br />
6-23 the best place I have found yet is up in the ShirVahl side of Paludal Caverns, though it is much easier if you have your healing song at the ready. at about 20th tier when you get dune with mushroom hall use your invis and look for the Shir'Nar, DO NOT fight the fiends unless you really really have too and then look for someone to cure disease as needed.( you MIGHT get up to 26 in here but you will have to try to break up the spawns on the back half of rogue camp 2, the ones around the camp fire. Use your snare song to keep from adds. Good luck) 
<br />
24-35 There are two good places for this. Najeana and , should you be in need of fresh air and sun light, the infected paw in the plans of Karana. Most know where this is but should you not, get to the stone bridge in North Karana then head south. You should run right into it. In Najeana start off with the terrors ( there are 4 of them ) and once you get up to about 30 then work on the 4 skellies that pop at the bottom of the stairs just past the DE Magi's and Ogre guards. take care on any side passages for there are floor traps that will drop you in a cell to be beat on by other ogre guards.At the paw try to stay out doors if you go in remember your run song will NOT be able to save you from trains.
<br />
36-40 one of the most profitable times I remember. Use your invis song to get to the bottom of Crystal Caverns. Put your back twards the little ice dwarf outpost in there and pull from the orcs you find in the hall. Kill all you can so that the dwarves will sell to you. Oh there is also a bank in that outpost to help get rid if the weight of coins you'll make.
<br />
41-50 Go back outside. Kill Ulthorks. Start with the hunters and work up to warriors. This will take some skill as they tend to get aid not only from their kind but from walruses as well. So keep the fighting tight. At 51 to about 55 if you like hunt up the Man -O- War's but take care, they hit HARD!
<br />
Well so far this is the best that I might do for you all. Tis my hope that this helps you and keeps you in good form. Best of luck my brothers and sisters.
<br />
At about 50th tier, should you wish to do so, is a fine time to start your epic quest as there are some parts that you can be no higher than 55th to gain. Again, Good Luck and may the gods favor you in a grand outcome.
<br />
Many that do not know us as a class make that mistake. But for those of you that have ever been in a duel with a bard, and one that knows his songs, their story soon changes.
<br />
Remember we can drain mana just about as fast as a dwarf can drain a liter of ale! We can also slow their attacks. Keep in mind that a bard does not look at his songs just as they are but other uses for the same song.Many of them have far more than just one use, if you look you'll see what i mean. For example, the charm songs not only make the mob your pet but will insure that someone will not KS you like as happens to many of the druids out there.
<br />
Just remember my young brothers and sisters, those people out there are how we make our true bread and wine so save some mobs for them. With our unspoken misunderstood power comes the responsibility too. We ALL are there for a good time, Lets be a PART of the fun we were ment to be!!
<br />

<br />
Hunt well and may the gods keep your purse full and your missed notes gone!
<br />
Cerik Doomedlute
<br />
52nd Tier Bard
<br />
P.S. Please post anything you feel I might have missed, My Fellow Bards and Master Bards. * Sweeping Bow * Hunt well and may your songs flow as free as the ale, your purse ever full and the sun shine on your backs.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
