				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: All Bards are not created equal, a Bards take on creation.<a name="40350"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 17 04 5:00 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Really it dosen't matter that much where you put poinst but my suggestion would be any of the above with the first stat being the most suggested.
<br />

<br />
Sta
<br />
Cha
<br />
Str
<br />
Int
<br />

<br />
I'm maxed str and dex now and high on int.  Sta takes the longest to max and gives you valuable Hp at all levels.  The other three depend on your preference.  Cha is nice to help with DI, lull, charm and other bardy things.  Str is nice mostly at lower levels for carrying things / armor if your not being PLed, not horribly important and Int is nice for a little more mana but not a killer either way.
<br />

<br />
Oh and bind wound is kind of useless past lower levels since we have our regen songs.
<br />

<br />
Past this really basic guide just go out and play your bard to figure out how it works.  If you level too fast take some time out and play some songs in tranq or the bazaar where you wont get in trouble to raise skills.  If you like to solo occasionally group to raise your defense and weapons.
<br />

<br />
The real skill is not creating your bard, its playing your bard.</span></td>
