				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: All Bards are not created equal, a Bards take on creation.<a name="40385"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 17 04 7:44 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Notice that for a solo bard the STA stat plays a larger role than with a grouping bard.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I find this to be reversed.
<br />
When I'm soloing, I'm kiting. Sometimes I'm fear kiting, sometimes I'm AE kiting, either way I don't really care how many HP I have. If I get stunned more than once while AE kiting, I die; if not, I live. Plus or minus 100 HP won't make a difference.
<br />
Sure, if you're melee-soloing, STA might matter, but melee-soloing accounts for a minority of the soloing exp of a lot of bards.
<br />
When I'm grouping, I'm pulling. Lower HP means the healers have to work harder to keep me alive after each pull. Especially if I pull a caster mob and he decides to nuke me a few before joining the party. That's when I want any HP I can get; in fact, I always make sure I get an HP buff before I start pulling.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">"And now for my next miracle, I will turn water... into funk!"
</span></td>
