		</table></td><td class="PanelBody" valign="Top"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" border="0" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: All Bards are not created equal, a Bards take on creation.<a name="40708"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 19 04 9:39 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I congratulate Cerik for starting a vigorous dialog. 
<br />

<br />
Very little of Cerik's post aligns with my experiences in-game solo'ing or grouping. Still, I suppose the advantage of free advice freely offered is that anyone can safely ignore it without much cost.
<br />

<br />
My two plat is: Bards seem to need to put points into DEX, CHA, INT, STR, STA, and I would argue, AGI. I have to agree that WIS is useless by all known or published accounts. It hardly seems to matter, since we have too many priority attributes to fill before we consider WIS, anyway.
<br />

<br />
As many have generously pointed out, we make up the difference in gear. The logical advice to the creation of the bard might seem to be &quot;Don't start one right away. Start something else, make a bunch of money. Then, twink out your bard.&quot;
<br />

<br />
Personally, I did not do it that way, and I have no regrets. I tend to think that un-twinked bards learn our class and gain confidence faster through the innovation and experimentation that results from poverty and necessity. Like most on this board, I can take care of myself empty-handed and without a stitch on my back.
<br />

<br />
Therefore, my creation guide would simply say, &quot;Pick a race that suits you and a starting location that appeals to you. Pick a gender that suits you. Pick a deity or don't as it suits your role-playing character. Half elf hats look stupid by most people's tastes, if that helps in any way.&quot;
<br />

<br />
And if it does not, remember it is free advice freely offered.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">"l'homme qui combat et des courses, celui est l'homme qui vit pour combattre un autre jour.-- Tenpole, Order of the Golden Staff, CZ Server</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
